title: The Black Poodle and Other Tales
creator: Anstey, F.
description: LibriVox recording of The Black Poodle and Other Tales, by F. Anstey. This is a collection of ten humorous short stories (Summary by Carolin) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librvox;audio book;audiobook;literature;humor;short story
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody:
A few of the stories were funny and a few were emotional. Agamemnon and the Curse of the Catafalques were very funny, I got a chuckle from both of those. 

The chapters read by the one reader I couldn't understand; her voice was too high and her accent too heavy. I skipped those. I liked Joyce's reading, she did a nice job.
